SUMMARY:Cat On A Hot Tin Roof
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270509T143000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270509T164500
DTSTAMP:20260715T051231Z
UID:occ-458@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Tennessee Williams' Pulitzer-winning drama of Maggie the Cat\,
  Brick\, and a family gathering thick with lies.\n\nTennessee Williams' 19
 55 drama\, winner of the Pulitzer Prize and his own personal favorite amon
 g his plays. On a Mississippi Delta plantation\, the family of cotton tyco
 on Big Daddy gathers for his birthday\, hiding what everyone but him knows
  about his health. At the center are Maggie the Cat and her husband Brick\
 , a drinking ex-football hero who won't touch her\, while his brother mane
 uvers for the family fortune. From Cherokee Theatre\; recommended for ages
  12 and up.
GEO:34.2365417;-84.4902423
LAST-MODIFIED:20260715T051050Z
LOCATION:Canton Theatre\, 171 E Main St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
